    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/77">Henricus</persName> divina favente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si locis divino cultui mancipatis regali
                        iuvamine proficimus, divina remuneratione id nobis recompensandum vere
                        scimus. Cunctis igitur deo nobisque nunc et in posterum militantibus pateat,
                        nos pro nostrae animae futura recompensatione et interventu fidelium
                        nostrorum <persName key="#Intercessory #Archbishops #Archchancellor"
                            ref="#people/1306">Annonis</persName>
                        <orgName>Coloniensis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> ceterorumque <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcoporum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ducum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchionum</rs> atque <rs key="#Count">comitum</rs>
                        confirmasse et penitus iure perpetuo corroborasse <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1471">sanctae <placeName ref="#places/594"
                                >Ravenati</placeName> aecclesiae</orgName> cui vocabulum est agia
                        Anastasis et domno <persName key="#Archbishops" ref="#people/4322"
                            >Heinrico</persName> eiusdem aecclesiae venerabili <rs
                            key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopo</rs> suisque successoribus omnes res
                        mobiles et inmobiles seu et quaecumque ab antecessoribus nostris regibus et
                        imperatoribus nec non Romane sedis apostolicis predicte Ravenati aecclesie
                        suisque presulibus preceptali institutione seu confirmatione sunt attributa,
                        siquidem episcopatus <rs key="#Monasteries">monasteria</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">aecclesias</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitates</rs> et <rs key="#Castle">castella</rs>
                        <rs key="#Slave">famulos</rs> et <rs key="#Slave">famulas</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs> etiam <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#estates/1478">
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Feretranum</placeName></geogName> cum <rs key="#Dioecesis"
                            >episcopatu</rs> suo et cum monasterio <orgName
                            key="#Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries">sancti Salvatoris</orgName>
                        in ipso comitatu posito, comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Castle #Tower #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1479">
                            <placeName key="#Castle #Tower #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/1890">Cesenatem</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Castle">castro vetere et novo</rs> et <rs key="#Tower"
                            >turribus</rs> ac omnibus sibi pertinentibus, comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Dioecesis #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/3913">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Dioecesis #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/4667">Ficoclensem</placeName></geogName> cum episcopatu
                        suo et <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripa</rs>,
                        episcopatum <orgName key="#Allocation_to_churches #Dioecesis"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/108">Regiensem</orgName> cum dono et
                        consecratione, sicut Otto noster antecessor imperator stabili manu
                        constituit, simulque comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#estates/3987">
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Decimanum</placeName></geogName>, comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#estates/3988">
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Trauersarie</placeName></geogName>, comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#estates/2409">
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#places/3512"
                                >Immolensem</placeName></geogName>, comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Fisheries #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2449">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Fisheries #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/485">Cunnaclensem</placeName></geogName> cum ripa et
                            <rs key="#Fisheries">piscariis</rs> suis, comitatum <geogName
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Fisheries #Comitatus #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/84">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Fisheries #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                ref="#places/80">Ferrarie</placeName></geogName> cum ripa et
                        piscariis suis nec non districtum <placeName key="#Walls #Ports #Mints"
                            ref="#places/594">Rauenne</placeName> cum <rs key="#Ports">portis</rs>
                        ripa et portubus <rs key="#Walls">muris publicaliis</rs> et omnibus <rs
                            key="#Teloneum">teloneis</rs> et <rs key="#Mints">moneta publica</rs>,
                        quam hinc inantea ibi fieri precepimus sub potestate prefate aecclesie
                        eiusque presulum. Concedimus etiam omnem potestatem in omnibus infra et
                        extra civitatem Ravennam, sicut nostri antecessores reges et imperatores
                        antea constituerunt, <rs key="#Massae">massam</rs> quoque quae vocatur
                            <geogName key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#estates/2479"
                                ><placeName key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#places/4600"
                                >Fiscalia</placeName></geogName> cum <placeName ref="#places/3520"
                            >Cornu ceruino</placeName>, monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Allocation_to_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sanctae
                            Marie in <placeName ref="#places/4179">Ponposa</placeName>
                        </orgName> cum omnibus rebus et pertinentiis suis, <geogName
                            key="#Ports #Fisheries #Shores" ref="#estates/2465"><placeName
                                key="#Ports #Shores #Fisheries" ref="#places/4887">portum
                                Uolane</placeName></geogName> integriter cum piscariis suis et omni
                            <rs key="#Shores">litore maris</rs> et portubus [u]s[que a]d portum
                        Ceruie et usque ad <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers">[Pu]nctarii</placeName>. Simulque donamus iuxta
                        au[ctoritate]m nostrorum antecessorum imperatorum abba[t]iam <orgName
                            key="#Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/3669"
                            >sancte Mariae positam in loco B[an]g[a]r[itiae</orgName>] cum dono et
                        consecratione <rs key="#Abbots">abbatum</rs> et cum omnibus pertinentiis
                        suis inter <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Padum</placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4646">At[is]am</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Rivers">fluvios</rs> sitis in <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines" ref="#estates/2420"><placeName key="#Fines"
                                ref="#places/3522">Adriensi</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Fines" ref="#estates/2410"><placeName key="#Fines"
                                ref="#places/80">Ferrariensi</placeName></geogName> et ubicumque
                        sint vel invente fuerint eiusdem abbatie proprietates. Preterea confirmamus
                        monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Allocation_to_churches #Districtio #Curtes #Castle"
                            >sancti Hilarii in Caligata </orgName> cum omni <rs key="#Districtio"
                            >districto</rs> et placito suo, <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs> et pertinentiis suis, monosteria <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Allocation_to_churches">sancti Thome
                            apostoli</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/3668"
                            >sancte Evfemie</orgName> infra <rs key="#Cities">civitatem</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/1806">Arrimini</placeName> cum omnibus
                        pertinentiis suis seu omnes res, quas <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Deacons"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> filius
                            <persName key="#Marquis/duke"><name ref="Martinus"
                            >Martini</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ducis</rs> Rauenati aecclesie contulit, et omnia,
                        que <persName key="#Countess"><name ref="Ingelrada"
                            >Ingelrada</name></persName> tenuit <rs key="#Countess">comitissa</rs> a
                            <rs key="#Sea">mari</rs> Adriano [u]sque ad Alpes, a fluvio <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3548">Reni</placeName> usque Potentiam, sicut
                        maximus Otto imperator in placito per legem investivit <persName
                            key="#Archbishops"><name ref="Petrus">Petrum</name></persName> Rauenatem
                        archiepiscopum suamque aecclesiam, itemque omnia, quae <persName
                            key="#Count"><name ref="Lambertus">Lantbertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> cum uxore vel filiis habuit a mari usque ad
                        Alpes et a Reno usque <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4609"
                            >Folium</placeName>, sicut precessor noster <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7">tercius Otto</persName> cesar sepe
                        dictae pro eorum culpis donavit aecclesie, nominatim vero comitatus
                            <geogName key="#Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus">
                            <placeName key="#Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus"
                            >Bobii</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Allocation_to_churches #Cities #Comitatus" ref="#estates/2459"
                                ><placeName key="#Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus"
                                ref="#places/3515">Foriliuii</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Allocation_to_churches #Cities #Comitatus" ref="#estates/2480"
                                ><placeName key="#Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus"
                                ref="#places/4602">Foripupulii</placeName></geogName> cum
                        civitatibus et districtibus eorum et omnibus eisdem pertinentibus. Haec
                        omnia confirmamus stabilique gradu corroboramus ipsi aecclesiae, omnia quae
                        antiquitus vel noviter tenuit vel tenet sive ei pertinet in tota <rs
                            key="#Marca/ducatum">marchia</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Marca/ducatum" ref="#estates/1406"><placeName
                                key="#Marca/ducatum" ref="#places/248"
                            >Camerini</placeName></geogName> per diversos comitatus et territoria,
                        videlicet <geogName key="#Comitatus #Fines" ref="#estates/3989"><placeName
                                key="#Comitatus #Fines" ref="#places/1816"
                            >Auximanum</placeName></geogName>, <geogName key="#Comitatus #Fines"
                            ref="#estates/3990"><placeName key="#Comitatus #Fines"
                                ref="#places/1810">Anconitanum</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus #Fines" ref="#estates/3991"><placeName
                                key="#Comitatus #Fines" ref="#places/1809"
                                >Senogalliensem</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus #Fines" ref="#estates/2481"><placeName
                                key="#Comitatus #Fines" ref="#places/1808"
                            >Fani</placeName></geogName> aliosque comitatus et nominatim ea omnia,
                        quae predictus domnus Heinricus archiepiscopus ad iura ipsius aecclesie
                        revocavit, massam scilicet <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Castle #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName key="#Massae #Castle #Allocation_to_churches">Aframanam que
                                vocatur Auximana</placeName>
                        </geogName>, in qua est castrum <placeName key="#Castle">Huboldi quod nunc
                            vocatur Gebehardi</placeName>, castellum <placeName key="#Castle"
                            >Ofanie</placeName> et massam <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rovssiani</placeName></geogName>, massam <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches">Merolanam que vocatur
                                de Senegallia</placeName></geogName>, curtem <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName key="#Curtes #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montonis</placeName></geogName>, massam <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Victoriadam</placeName></geogName> et massam <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName key="#Massae #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Salam</placeName></geogName>, terram Fani, castrum <placeName
                            key="#Castle">Tuderiani</placeName>, territorium Pupiliense. Haec omnia
                        cum omnibus rebus possessionibus et pertinentiis suis emissa nostra
                        preceptione atque regali edicto prenominatam aecclesiam habere firmiterque
                        tenere precipimus. Si quis igitur huius nostrae preceptionis violator
                        extiterit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">mille libras auri
                            purissimi</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere nostrae</rs>
                        et medietatem <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">predictae
                            aecclesiae</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur et ab omnibus diligentius
                        observetur, hanc cartam inde conscribi manuque propria corroborantes sigilli
                        nostri inpressione iussimus insigniri. Signum domni Heinrici quarti regis.
                        (M.) <persName key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/4301">
                            Wigbertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice Annonis <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> recognovi. Data est VIII
                        kal. iulii anno dominicae incarnationis millesimo LXIII, indictione I, anno
                        ordinationis domni Heinrici quarti regis VIII, regni vero VI; actum
                            <placeName>Altstet</placeName>; in dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
